Ticket ID: MOB-CONF-2026-02-IP16PM-PERF
Title: iPhone 16 Pro Max — Manual Max Performance Configuration Profile
Classification: Mobile Performance Configuration Standard
Date: February 2026
Status: Manual Activation Required
System Identification
	• Device: iPhone 16 Pro Max
	• Manufacturer: Apple Inc.
	• Operating System: iOS (latest available version at the time)
	• Usage: Primary personal and productivity device

Executive Summary
This ticket documents the step-by-step procedure to manually activate Max Performance Mode on the iPhone 16 Pro Max. The profile prioritizes CPU/GPU responsiveness, minimal background activity, manual automation control, and reduced indexing and suggestion services, with battery optimization as a secondary concern.

1. Activation Procedure
1.1 Connectivity Configuration
	• Airplane Mode: OFF (enable manually only if required)
	• Wi-Fi: ON, Auto-Join ON (trusted networks only)
	• Bluetooth: OFF (enable only when using AirPods, car, or file transfer)
	• Mobile Service:
		○ Mobile Data = ON
		○ Wi-Fi Assist = ON
		○ iCloud Drive = ON
		○ iCloud Backup = ON
		○ Mobile Data Usage Statistics = enabled
	• Personal Hotspot: OFF (enable manually only if needed)
1.2 Battery Configuration
	• Low Power Mode = OFF
	• Battery Percentage = ON
1.3 Background Process Elimination
	• Background App Refresh: OFF for all apps and global toggle
	• Siri Suggestions & Indexing:
		○ Disable all suggestion and learning options
		○ Disable “Learn from this App” and app-specific suggestions
1.4 Display Performance Configuration
	• Auto-Brightness = OFF
	• Reduce White Point = ON (slider 40%)
	• Increase Contrast = ON
	• Bold Text = ON (restart required)
	• Reduce Transparency = OFF
1.5 Motion & Rendering
	• Reduce Motion = OFF
	• Limit Frame Rate = OFF
	• Dim Flashing Lights = OFF
	• Auto-Play Animated Images, Video Previews, Message Effects = ON
	• Full 120Hz ProMotion retained
1.6 Audio & Call Handling
	• Background Sounds = OFF
	• Live Listen = OFF
	• Mono Audio = OFF
	• Voice Isolation = ON
	• Headphone Notifications = OFF
	• Call Audio Routing = Automatic
	• Auto-Answer Calls = OFF
	• Flash for Alerts = ON (disable if instability observed)
1.7 Face ID Optimization
	• Require Attention for Face ID = ON
	• Attention-Aware Features = ON
	• Haptic on Successful Authentication = OFF
1.8 Siri & Voice Configuration
	• Apple Intelligence = ON
	• Press Side Button for Siri = ON
	• Type to Siri = ON
	• Always Listen for “Siri” = OFF
	• Allow Siri When Locked = ON
	• Announce Calls = Always
	• ChatGPT Extension = ON, Confirm Requests = ON

2. Final Validation Checklist
After completing all steps, confirm:
☑ Background App Refresh = OFF
☑ Bluetooth = OFF
☑ Low Power Mode = OFF
☑ Siri Suggestions = OFF
☑ Auto Brightness = OFF
☑ All app indexing disabled
☑ Wi-Fi ON
☑ Performance stable

3. Operational Characteristics of Max Performance Mode
	• Minimal background CPU wakeups
	• Reduced indexing and suggestion learning
	• No passive microphone listening
	• Full refresh rate maintained
	• Controlled radio usage
	• Manual power management

Risk Level: Low
System Status: Stable, Operational, Ready for High-Performance Tasks
Conclusion
The Max Performance Mode is now fully configured for peak CPU/GPU responsiveness, minimal background load, and complete manual control, while maintaining full 120Hz ProMotion and operational stability.
